The Finn Hall Farm was established in 1920 by our immigrated family from Finland. The refurbished Barn was originally built to milk cows and store milk going to market.
The Barn includes upstairs loft lounge and dining area, the downstairs bath house in the main barn, and the rustic privy near the stairs. The outdoor patio area & silo around back.
The loft features: comfy queen bed, electric fireplace, fold out couch,  lounge chairs, record player/stereo, and kitchenette.
The queen size bed is super comfy and cozy. The side cabinets can hold some of your belongings. There are extra blankets should you need.

The Kitchenette- A room with a Sunrise View! In the dining area you'll find a toaster oven, microwave, mini-fridge, coffee maker & grinder, dishes and few essentials like whole bean french roast coffee & cream.
The couch is easy to fold down into a large single bed. There are sheets, comforter and mattress pad in the trunk nearby.
The electric fireplace makes the space extra cozy on a chilly evening.
You'll have amazing views right from your bed in the morning or lounging in the sitting area.
The small deck is perfect for watching the sunset and drinking coffee overlooking the farm.
The bath house is located downstairs in the former milk house.

The bath house down stairs in the main barn includes a rustic shower, a vintage sink to clean up by, mirror and lounge/yoga space. Fresh towels and robes are available for your use including shampoo, soap and cleaning supplies.
Get your hot shower while glamping!
The vintage sink overlooks the garden. You can bring your dishes down from the loft to wash and fill up your water pitcher to take back up.
The rustic privy is a clean and private sani-can that is well maintained. It is located downstairs from the loft with easy access near the stairs. Headlamps provided for night time use.

The outdoor patio, located behind the barn, is private from other residents. Although you might see some friendly cows. It is equipped with fire pit, charcoal grill, and dining set. Pick fresh raspberries in season.
The deck overlooks the cow pasture, corral, silo and patio area. Be sure to check out the secret silo garden!

You'll be surrounded by 60 acres of preserved farmland with amazing views of the Olympic Mountains. In addition to cows munching lazily in fields there is an abundance of native birds including quail, eagles, and hawks.

Explore the common area including refurbished vintage caboose, the 'Crooked' house full of antique farm tools and memorabilia, the orchard and berry patch. Get a massage with Suzie in the Studio. (Peak a Boo water views from deck).
From the road you will be able to see the Barn as you enter the driveway. Drive straight ahead to your home away from home.
There is plenty of space to park on the grass next to Barn.

Locals collect seaweed and hang them under the sun to get dried seaweed.
